The '''2002–03''' season of the '''Norwegian Premier League''', the highest [[bandy]] league for men in [[Norway]].
16 games were played, with 2 points given for wins and 1 for draws. [[Mjøndalen IF|Mjøndalen]] won the league. No team was relegated; as the bottom team survived a playoff round. Instead the league was expanded with one extra team from the next season.
