{{Infobox football club | clubname = Rangers | fullname = Rangers Football Club | nickname = | founded = 1889 | ground = [[Rand Stadium]], [[Johannesburg]] | capacity = 25000 | chairman = | manager = | pattern_la1=_black_stripes|pattern_b1=_threebluestripes|pattern_ra1=_black_stripes||pattern_so1=_blacktop| leftarm1=FFFFFF|body1=FFFFFF|rightarm1=FFFFFF|shorts1=FFFFFF|socks1=FFFFFF| }}
'''Rangers FC''' is a [[South Africa]]n [[football (soccer)]] club based in [[Johannesburg]]. Rangers FC won the [[Castle Cup football|Castle Cup]] in [[Castle Cup football 1959|1959]] and played the final in 1967. Their best season in the [[National Football League (South Africa)|NFL]] was the inaugural season in 1959, when they finished Runners-up to [[Durban City F.C. (1959)|Durban City]]. The club merged with [[Johannesburg Ramblers]] for the 1963-season.
